WEBVTT

00:33.730 --> 00:44.304
Welcome back to our study of the book of Proverbs and we are still in chapter 7 and we are going to read right now in verses 10 through 21.

00:44.645 --> 00:46.467
Let's read.

00:48.089 --> 00:51.854
And behold, a woman comes to meet him dressed as a harlot and cunning of heart.

00:52.515 --> 00:54.178
She is boisterous and rebellious.

00:54.218 --> 00:55.760
Her feet do not remain at home.

00:56.421 --> 01:00.466
She is now in the streets, now in the squares and lurks by every corner.

01:01.186 --> 01:03.268
So she seizes him and kisses him.

01:03.288 --> 01:07.954
And with a brazen face, she says to him, I was due to offer peace offerings.

01:08.454 --> 01:10.056
Today I have paid my vows.

01:10.677 --> 01:15.022
Therefore I have come out to meet you, to seek your presence earnestly.

01:15.302 --> 01:16.323
And I have found you.

01:16.363 --> 01:22.390
I have spread my couch with coverings and my colored linens of eat with colored linens of Egypt.

01:22.971 --> 01:26.135
I have sprinkled my bed with mirth, alloys and cinnamon.

01:26.675 --> 01:29.138
Come let us drink our fill of love until morning.

01:29.570 --> 01:31.753
Let us delight ourselves with caresses.

01:32.293 --> 01:34.836
For my husband is not at home.

01:34.977 --> 01:36.779
He has gone on a long journey.

01:37.640 --> 01:39.462
He has taken a bag of money with him.

01:40.003 --> 01:41.705
At the full moon, he will come home.

01:42.886 --> 01:45.389
With her many persuasions, she entices him.

01:46.150 --> 01:48.513
With her flattering lips, she seduces him.

01:49.955 --> 01:50.455
Let's pray.

01:54.040 --> 01:59.346
Father, I pray that you would help us to teach this passage

02:00.034 --> 02:29.938
in a way that it would be of great help, Lord, that it would be of great help to your people, to the young boys and girls that are listening to the teenagers, to the parents, Lord, that we would understand the dangers, the great dangers of sin, that we'd learn to identify those dangers and stand against them, even separate ourselves from them.

02:30.914 --> 02:44.867
Lord help help myself help me help the people who are listening to walk not as the foolish, but as those who are wise who understand the will of God and obey it.

02:45.808 --> 02:50.753
And Lord also increase our fear of the in Jesus name.

02:52.074 --> 02:52.414
Amen.

02:53.515 --> 02:54.877
We are in verse 14.

02:54.897 --> 03:00.722
And the woman comes to this this young boy and she says this.

03:01.954 --> 03:04.016
I was due to offer peace offerings.

03:04.116 --> 03:05.918
Today I have paid my vows.

03:06.699 --> 03:12.064
Now, as we've said, this is a woman who's unfaithful to God.

03:12.104 --> 03:14.407
She's unfaithful to her husband.

03:14.627 --> 03:16.689
She's unfaithful to her children.

03:17.710 --> 03:29.682
We could say she's unfaithful to her tribe and she's being unfaithful to this young man because she's trying to get him to do something that is against the will of God.

03:30.146 --> 03:31.608
Now, here's the amazing thing.

03:31.688 --> 03:37.134
In verse 14, we see that she pretends to be religious.

03:38.215 --> 03:40.878
She says, I was due to offer peace offerings.

03:41.279 --> 03:43.541
Today, I've paid my vows.

03:44.442 --> 03:45.483
I've made my offerings.

03:45.583 --> 03:47.005
I've made my sacrifices.

03:47.125 --> 03:50.769
I've done the right religious thing.

03:51.770 --> 03:54.894
Now, do you see the contrast externally?

03:55.755 --> 03:58.418
A person does religious things.

03:58.882 --> 04:06.773
externally a person may even profess faith in Christ or say that they are a Christian or say that they belong to a church.

04:07.414 --> 04:15.204
But the real proof of their Christianity, of their faith is the way they live.

04:15.885 --> 04:19.691
Now with her, we see something throughout all these characteristics.

04:20.211 --> 04:22.835
And that is the word autonomy.

04:25.258 --> 04:28.082
It's kind of a self law.

04:28.834 --> 04:30.496
self-government.

04:31.477 --> 04:37.103
She claims to know God, but she lives in a way that is contrary to God.

04:37.544 --> 04:49.457
She has not put herself under God's governance, under God's law, but she pretends to know God and yet lives under a law to herself.

04:50.298 --> 04:57.266
You know, sometimes I say this, many people who claim to worship God, here's what they've done.

04:58.018 --> 05:00.020
They're not worshiping the God of the Bibles.

05:00.040 --> 05:01.422
Matter of fact, they don't even like Him.

05:03.364 --> 05:09.470
They've made a God in their own image, and then they worship the God that they've made.

05:09.550 --> 05:10.391
That's what they've done.

05:11.493 --> 05:19.221
Also, they've kind of made up their own commands, and then they follow the commands they've made.

05:20.442 --> 05:27.730
The test, young person, as to whether or not you're a true Christian, the test as to whether your faith

05:28.354 --> 05:36.545
is reliable and real, is that not only you claim to know God, but that you know the God of the Bible.

05:37.366 --> 05:40.250
And not only that, you know His will.

05:40.851 --> 05:42.833
You recognize it is right.

05:43.314 --> 05:44.836
You seek to obey it.

05:45.437 --> 05:54.469
And when you do not obey it, when you fail, you repent, you ask for forgiveness, and you begin again.

05:55.109 --> 05:55.570
This is

05:55.842 --> 05:58.526
To me, verse 14 is absolutely astounding.

05:59.347 --> 06:08.080
She's asking Him to disobey one of the most important commands in the 10 commandments.

06:08.601 --> 06:12.387
It has to do with fidelity or faithfulness in marriage.

06:13.128 --> 06:21.901
She's asking Him to break this command even when the penalty for breaking this command in the Old Testament was death.

06:23.022 --> 06:25.426
And she's doing it all the while.

06:25.698 --> 06:30.445
She claims to be religious and obedient.

06:31.126 --> 06:36.353
Do you see how deceptive sin can be?

06:37.334 --> 06:41.921
So I ask you again, do you claim to know God?

06:42.442 --> 06:44.364
Do you claim to believe in Christ?

06:45.646 --> 06:46.527
Do you go to church?

06:47.188 --> 06:48.290
Well, all that's wonderful.

06:48.831 --> 06:50.193
But now here's the true test.

06:50.753 --> 06:54.098
What is your relationship with the commands of God?

06:54.370 --> 06:55.952
with the commands of Christ.

06:56.853 --> 07:00.118
Are you walking an obedience?

07:01.019 --> 07:01.980
There's the question.

07:02.801 --> 07:03.963
Now, let's go on.

07:08.209 --> 07:11.093
Here's another characteristic of the woman in verse 15.

07:12.154 --> 07:20.826
She says to this young man, therefore I have come out to meet you to seek your presence earnestly and I have found you.

07:21.266 --> 07:22.167
Do you know what she's doing?

07:22.568 --> 07:24.050
She's flattering him.

07:24.226 --> 07:27.970
And she's making him feel special.

07:29.192 --> 07:30.333
That's what the devil will do.

07:30.954 --> 07:32.135
That's what sinners will do.

07:32.155 --> 07:39.844
That's what the world will do until it uses you up and you're of no use anymore.

07:40.184 --> 07:43.849
She says, I've come out to meet you to seek your presence earnestly.

07:44.089 --> 07:45.571
And she says, I found you.

07:45.811 --> 07:48.434
It's almost as if she's saying, um,

07:49.634 --> 07:52.057
You know, I was seeking for you and seeking for you.

07:52.377 --> 07:53.258
And here you are.

07:53.578 --> 07:54.359
I found you.

07:54.639 --> 07:55.661
What a great prize.

07:56.722 --> 07:57.803
It's almost as if too.

07:57.863 --> 08:01.066
She's saying, God helped me find you.

08:01.927 --> 08:03.289
And we know that's not the case.

08:04.130 --> 08:06.032
So I want you to think about something.

08:06.512 --> 08:07.453
Listen to what she says.

08:09.155 --> 08:13.400
I've come out to meet you to find you, to seek your presence.

08:14.101 --> 08:16.323
Imagine a hunter saying that to a deer.

08:17.785 --> 08:19.026
I've come out to meet you.

08:19.266 --> 08:23.091
I've been looking all over for him and now I have found you.

08:23.372 --> 08:24.914
Would that be good news for a deer?

08:25.955 --> 08:29.059
Or imagine a spider saying that to a fly.

08:29.981 --> 08:33.545
I spread this web all across these leaves.

08:34.146 --> 08:41.196
I waited and waited and hoped that you would come and now you have come and I have found you.

08:42.097 --> 08:42.998
Just think about that.

08:43.859 --> 08:48.786
That's what's going on here because she is not seeking for him.

08:49.282 --> 08:52.466
in order to bring him into a right relationship with God.

08:52.506 --> 08:56.290
She's not looking for him in order to help him grow in Christ.

08:56.731 --> 09:02.417
She is looking for him in order to use him to pull him away from the paths of God.

09:02.758 --> 09:05.761
And it will eventually lead to his destruction.

09:06.602 --> 09:11.047
And once you think about this, we go back to Genesis chapter three and what happens?

09:11.548 --> 09:13.650
Satan comes out to meet Adam and Eve.

09:14.652 --> 09:16.754
It's almost as if he said the same thing.

09:17.122 --> 09:24.270
I've been searching for you and searching for you and here now I have found you.

09:25.472 --> 09:32.019
She's saying, I have found you and now I'm going to take you away where you will experience all kinds of wonderful pleasures.

09:32.420 --> 09:34.723
Satan comes out and what does he do?

09:35.223 --> 09:38.107
I have found you and I am here to do what?

09:38.527 --> 09:41.230
To save you from God.

09:42.532 --> 09:44.434
That's basically what he's saying.

09:45.602 --> 09:48.385
because when he says, why don't you eat of this tree?

09:49.286 --> 09:50.888
Now don't you think about this for a moment.

09:52.510 --> 09:59.938
God gave Adam and Eve every tree in the entire world except one.

10:00.719 --> 10:11.011
Now he made those trees, they didn't, and he gives every tree he ever made to them to enjoy and to eat from, except one.

10:12.052 --> 10:13.714
But Satan comes and says,

10:14.274 --> 10:18.379
Did God really prohibit you from participating in this tree?

10:19.020 --> 10:19.741
I don't think so.

10:19.841 --> 10:21.222
He wouldn't do something like that.

10:22.063 --> 10:24.366
But then when they say, well, yes, he did.

10:24.406 --> 10:32.116
Then he turns it around and says, well, isn't that kind of cruel of God that he would keep things from you?

10:32.756 --> 10:37.943
That's one of the things that you've got to realize about Satan, about sinners and about the world.

10:38.483 --> 10:43.890
They will oftentimes come to save you from God.

10:44.770 --> 11:00.124
Or if you're a Christian who's serious about knowing the commands of God and following them, they will come to you to try to save you from your rigid religion that's keeping you from having all the fun that they have.

11:00.925 --> 11:02.386
Do you see how deceptive it is?

11:03.187 --> 11:06.050
So in verse 14, what's going on?

11:06.530 --> 11:11.275
She appears as a very, very religious person, but she's not.

11:12.216 --> 11:14.738
In verse 15, what's going on?

11:15.010 --> 11:16.071
Oh, it's all about you.

11:16.111 --> 11:17.593
I've come out to find you.

11:17.693 --> 11:19.595
I am so happy that I have found you.

11:19.615 --> 11:21.657
You're so special to me.

11:22.678 --> 11:29.166
But in reality, it's like the spider saying that to the fly or the hunter saying that to the deer.

11:29.466 --> 11:35.052
I'm excited because I found you and now I'm going to devour you.

11:35.493 --> 11:38.116
Now, the next one is very, very important.

11:38.136 --> 11:40.038
Look at verses 16 through 18.

11:41.740 --> 11:43.922
I have spread my couch with covering.

11:44.290 --> 11:49.438
With colored linens of Egypt, I've sprinkled my bed with mirth, alloys, and cinnamon.

11:51.000 --> 11:54.525
Come, let us drink our fill of love until morning.

11:54.585 --> 11:57.389
Let us delight ourselves with caresses.

11:58.451 --> 12:11.730
I've written here, like the unfaithful woman, the world beautifies the very evil that God hates, and that brings death and eternal condemnation.

12:12.322 --> 12:22.072
You see, she's asking him to break one of the most important commands in all the Bible that have to do with being faithful in marriage.

12:22.352 --> 12:28.378
She's saying, break that command, break it, but it will be beautiful.

12:29.359 --> 12:30.801
I've decorated everything.

12:31.561 --> 12:40.050
My dear friend, it doesn't matter how beautiful it appears.

12:40.802 --> 12:49.331
If it is contrary to the Word of God, if it's contrary to the will of God, it will end in death.

12:49.791 --> 12:51.012
And you need to understand that.

12:52.013 --> 13:01.863
The world, you know, this is something about the world's propaganda is incredible.

13:02.724 --> 13:08.530
The signs leading to hell are absolutely gorgeous.

13:09.410 --> 13:18.906
And they make promises of life and of meaning and of purpose and of pleasure and of entertainment and of enjoyment.

13:19.507 --> 13:23.073
The signs are absolutely gorgeous.

13:25.217 --> 13:35.634
But the real thing is sin, death, the grave and hell.

13:36.898 --> 13:39.902
And so it doesn't matter how much she beautifies all of this.

13:40.943 --> 13:45.589
It's still disobedience to the commands of God.

13:46.229 --> 13:57.704
Now also let's go and look at verse 19 through 20 and we'll see here that the world seeks out every opportunity to escape from God's morality and into sin.

13:57.764 --> 14:00.567
Listen to what she says, for my husband is not at home.

14:01.008 --> 14:03.331
He has gone on a long journey.

14:03.811 --> 14:06.194
He has taken a bag of money with him.

14:06.498 --> 14:09.944
At the full moon, he will come home.

14:10.304 --> 14:15.513
Now, I want us to kind of tear this apart because we're going to see all kinds of very, very important truths here.

14:16.976 --> 14:22.825
First of all, we see that she has no moral convictions of her own.

14:25.289 --> 14:30.418
So while her husband is there, she's like a trapped animal.

14:32.066 --> 14:33.949
She doesn't run out into the streets.

14:34.129 --> 14:36.973
She doesn't do bad things while her husband is there.

14:37.393 --> 14:44.483
But the moment he leaves, she's like a caged animal that found a way to get the door open.

14:44.884 --> 14:52.535
And as soon as that door is open, she runs straight out to what she thinks is freedom, even though it is only sin.

14:53.316 --> 14:55.819
Now, I want to share something with you.

14:58.703 --> 15:00.626
If you're raised in a Christian home,

15:01.154 --> 15:10.244
If your parents are Christians, if they love the Lord, if they're trying to raise you, that's a wonderful thing.

15:10.324 --> 15:13.608
But at the same time, it should actually be a little bit fearful.

15:14.369 --> 15:14.689
Why?

15:15.710 --> 15:29.906
I have seen so many children, so many homeschool children, that while they're at home, until they're 18 or so, while they're at home, they act very

15:30.306 --> 15:31.067
obedient.

15:31.848 --> 15:35.312
They go to church because their parents tell them we're going to church.

15:35.713 --> 15:38.736
They read the Bible because their parents tell them to read the Bible.

15:39.117 --> 15:44.183
They avoid certain sins because their parents tell them to avoid certain sins.

15:44.524 --> 15:56.118
But soon as they come out from under the guidance and governance of their parents, they run wild like some rabbit dog in the yard.

15:56.378 --> 15:59.282
They run straight for the world.

15:59.874 --> 16:00.915
So what does that tell us?

16:01.896 --> 16:09.623
Young person, the most important thing right now to you is not outward conformity to your parent's standard.

16:10.764 --> 16:24.417
Even though you should conform to that standard, the most important thing is for you to look inward and ask yourself, am I doing this because I truly have a relationship with Jesus Christ?

16:25.318 --> 16:25.978
I love him.

16:27.059 --> 16:29.842
I love his commandments and I want to follow him.

16:33.122 --> 16:49.537
If you cannot say that and you realize that all your obedience, all your church going, all your homework, everything that you do, all your obedience is just because you have to, just because you do not have a choice.

16:50.298 --> 16:56.804
If that's the case with you, you should be very, very, very afraid.

16:57.225 --> 16:58.065
And what should you do?

16:59.026 --> 16:59.927
You should be honest.

17:00.968 --> 17:02.930
First of all, you should be honest to God.

17:03.778 --> 17:08.384
You should say, God, I'm here acting this way.

17:08.725 --> 17:12.530
I know it only because I'm like an animal in a cage.

17:13.852 --> 17:17.397
I'm young and my parents have control over me.

17:18.438 --> 17:25.709
But I know in my heart that if I get a little bit of freedom, I'm going to run as far away from you as I can.

17:26.390 --> 17:29.554
I'm going to run as far into the world as I can.

17:29.922 --> 17:34.048
say that to God, confess it to God, say cry out to God.

17:34.409 --> 17:35.290
God help me.

17:35.971 --> 17:39.436
God, please change my heart.

17:40.518 --> 17:41.620
Please change my heart.

17:42.481 --> 17:52.857
But also go to your parents and just be honest and say things like, you know, I appreciate you and I appreciate what you're trying to do.

17:55.321 --> 17:57.003
But this is still not in my heart.

17:58.105 --> 17:58.866
Pray for me.

17:59.938 --> 18:08.088
I'm afraid, mom and dad, I'm afraid that if you were to turn away, I would run like an animal out of a cage and I don't want to be that way.

18:08.409 --> 18:09.250
I know it's wrong.

18:10.431 --> 18:14.597
So pray for me, intercede for me, teach me, help me.

18:16.880 --> 18:24.169
Pray that God will work in my heart so that I will love him when no one is looking.

18:25.671 --> 18:27.954
I will hate sin when no one is looking.

18:28.578 --> 18:39.935
I will love righteousness when no one is looking and I'll do all that because it's in my heart, because God has saved me and God has changed me.

18:40.656 --> 18:54.877
In Psalms 32 9, it says, do not be as the horse or as the mule, which have no understanding whose trappings include bit and bridle to hold them in check.

18:54.897 --> 18:58.002
Otherwise, they will not come near to you.

18:59.490 --> 19:03.454
Do you see how that may apply to many of you who are listening right now?

19:04.976 --> 19:07.419
Yeah, outwardly your obedient.

19:08.801 --> 19:15.408
Yes, you do go to church and Sunday school and you do your homeschool curriculum and you read your Bible.

19:15.608 --> 19:16.109
Wonderful.

19:17.010 --> 19:23.217
But you know that if your parents weren't there and struck you to do so holding you accountable that you wouldn't.

19:24.118 --> 19:27.762
That means that your heart has still not been changed.

19:29.346 --> 19:34.675
And so you should cry out to God and also seek counsel from your parents.

19:35.115 --> 19:41.045
And then maybe with your parents seek counsel from one of the pastors or elders of your church.

19:41.966 --> 19:42.327
All right.

19:43.168 --> 19:45.252
Well, I hope that this has been helpful.

19:45.312 --> 19:47.015
And I hope it's been a wake up call.

19:47.656 --> 19:56.530
We started out in verse 14 with a woman who appears very religious, super spiritual.

19:57.602 --> 19:59.224
But she's exposed quickly.

19:59.304 --> 19:59.585
Why?

19:59.885 --> 20:03.249
She doesn't love the commands of God, nor does she seek to obey them.

20:03.770 --> 20:12.481
We see someone who is making sin appear to be beautiful, not realizing that it's actually kind of what Jesus said, isn't it?

20:12.501 --> 20:17.587
That the Pharisees and the scribes, they decorated these tombs.

20:18.489 --> 20:20.251
They made them so beautiful.

20:21.112 --> 20:25.938
But inside those tombs, there was nothing but rotten bones.

20:26.594 --> 20:31.801
And then we see someone who says, you know, no one's here.

20:32.242 --> 20:33.283
My husband's gone.

20:33.363 --> 20:35.346
There's no one here to hold me accountable.

20:35.947 --> 20:37.449
There's no one here to judge me.

20:37.489 --> 20:39.872
Now I'm free.

20:40.433 --> 20:44.038
And since I'm free, I'm going to run straight into sin.

20:45.300 --> 20:47.163
Oh, please, I beg you, be careful.

20:47.884 --> 20:48.504
Be careful.

20:49.065 --> 20:55.474
If that's you, go to your parents, go to your pastor, tell them the truth.

20:55.938 --> 20:58.521
Ask for prayer, ask for instruction.

20:58.842 --> 20:59.543
Go to God.

21:00.124 --> 21:02.527
Lord, change my heart.

21:03.488 --> 21:03.849
All right?

21:04.489 --> 21:04.990
Let's pray.

21:08.595 --> 21:11.058
Father, I come before you, and I pray.

21:12.580 --> 21:22.834
Lord, I am sure that there are some who listen to this, who outwardly appear obedient, but inwardly,

21:25.154 --> 21:26.375
They just want to escape.

21:26.415 --> 21:31.621
They want to run from righteousness and into sin.

21:33.002 --> 21:49.039
I pray, dear God, that you would work in their heart, that you would change their heart, change them in such a way that they would hate the sin they once loved, and love for the righteousness they once hated.

21:49.059 --> 21:51.922
Lord, I ask this in Jesus' name, amen.

